HEADWORD: manicurist
<hw>man"i*cur`ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>manus</ets> hand + <ets>curare</ets> to cure.]</ety> <def>A person
who makes a business of taking care of people's hands, especially their
fingernails; -- formerly called a <altname>manicure</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

